The Supreme Court on Tuesday affirmed the election of Governor Samuel Ortom of Benue state in the March 9, 2019 governorship poll. Ortom, the candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), was dragged to the apex court by his arch-rival in the election, Emmanuel Jime,  of the All Progressives Congress (APC).  Details later… Akwa Ibom: Supreme Court affirms Udom’s election BREAKING: Supreme Court dismisses appeal against PDP’s Bala Mohammed Supreme Court ends Abraham's dream to unseat Gov Akeredolu